	<td bgcolor="#F7F7F7" width="100%" valign="top">
	<font size="1" face="Verdana, Arial"><img src="../ubb/icons/icon1.gif" alt="Post" border="0"> <b>CH tactics</b></font>
	<p><font size="2" face="Verdana, Arial">Posted for one of our guild raid leaders .-)<br />
<br />
Aengel<br />
58 cleric <br />
Dragons of Saint George, Quellious<br />
<br />
----------------------------------------<br />
<br />
Hello everybody,<br />
<br />
aye another CH question but I wanted to see how experienced guilds/Clerics resolve this.<br />
<br />
Whenever a CH is used it generates a certain amount of hate. When used in a XP group it usually doesnt affect the cleric as it is cast later in the fight so the tank had more then enough time to build up hate of his own to keep aggro. <br />
<br />
But if you use a CH right from the start of the fight, chances are high that the cleric gets jumped and killed before aggro can be established.<br />
Splashhealing instead of CHing either doesnt keep the tank alive or generates too much aggro after a few casts = same result.<br />
<br />
Now, in a CH rotation clerics are FORCED to use CH spells right from the start.<br />
<br />
How does your guild handle this?<br />
<br />
- do you have a "sacrifice" which is casting first CH<br />
- do you use a combination of splashhealing + CH to keep the MA up? how many clerics are used in that case?<br />
- how does your guild starts a CH rotation? Is the MA required to survive the first 10 seconds on his own?<br />
- in case of the Vindicator where a 3 to 4 second rotation is suggested how does the MA survive long enough to get the first CH? Timing (start to cast 6 seconds early)? How do you prevent aggro ping ponging then?<br />
<br />
The biggest problem we have right now is to get a CH rotation going, our members are drilled into the use of their keys and are disciplined enough to keep a fixed order and delay up but more often then not the MA (lv 60 Warlord) goes down quicker then the first CH can connect.<br />
<br />
Any suggestions about "tricks of the trade" or general suggestions would appreciated  <img src="http://eqcleric.gameglow.com/ubb/smile.gif" border="0" alt=""><br />
<br />
Thank you <br />
<br />
Sharph<br />
<br /></font></p>
	
