	<td bgcolor="#DEDFDF" width="100%" valign="top">
	<font size="1" face="Verdana, Arial"><img src="../ubb/icons/icon1.gif" alt="Post" border="0"> <b></b></font>
	<p><font size="2" face="Verdana, Arial">My guild has only a limited number of clerics at this time...we have around five or so that can be relied upon for big raids. Needless to say, we sometimes wind up with all the clerics in rotation, with no time to heal anyone else but the MT. Thus, we often have to rely on /assist healing from our many druids and shamans to help fill in the gaps, both in our rotation and in terms of covering everyone else.<br />
<br />
As for handling the initial aggro of CH, we usually don't have a problem. Our usual MT is a heavily-armored ogre with a Willsapper and Frostbringer. We pre-buff him with enchanter Runes, and he opens with Defensive. This gives him time to build aggro (and hopefully get a Willsapper proc) before we start up the CH chain.<br />
<br />
A note about Willsapper: If your guild MT doesn't have one, GET ONE. It has a powerful slow/debuff proc that is pretty much an aggro lock for the rest of the fight if it goes off.<br />
<br />
Hope this helps. <br />
<br />
------------------<br />
