<tr>
	<td bgcolor="#F7F7F7" width="175" valign="top" nowrap>
	<a name="post66569"></a>
	
	<font size="2" face="Verdana, Arial"><b>Aldur</b></font><br>
	<font size="1" face="Verdana, Arial">Ragefire Camper</font><br>
	<p>
	<font size="1" face="Verdana, Arial">Registered: Mar 2000<br>
	Location: <br>
	Posts: 1273</font></td>
	
	<td bgcolor="#F7F7F7" width="100%" valign="top">
	<font size="1" face="Verdana, Arial"><img src="../ubb/icons/icon1.gif" alt="Post" border="0"> <b></b></font>
	<p><font size="2" face="Verdana, Arial">We have a number of ways of dealing with it.<br />
<br />
If you don't need to worry about ae so much, then often we get a monk to tank.  Its a simply process the monk pulls.  Gets to where the MT is then turns around and beats up the mob using riposte disc or stone stance or anything to make sure he survives for a reasonable period of time.  The MT is also attacking at the same time - and the chain has already started on him (though you cancel CH's that don't heal anything).  When the monk starts to get seriously hit and after he has used mend, he fd's and it flicks onto the MT (or you could use ae taunt).  This gives you 15 seconds ish of time where the MT is generating agro but is not generating heal agro for the clerics.  This should hopefully be enough.<br />
<br />
Or you can use hybrids.  Last st raid I was on none of our warriors wanted to go.  Feeling a bit aphrensive as I can get agro from the damage healed on a warrior (along with what type of damage 4 flurries in 10 seconds would be on a hybrid), we set up a generous rotation on the hybrid.  I was expecting to get agro.<br />
<br />
Surprisingly enough the only time in the entire raid the agro slipped is when our sk MT went ld.  We normally are very careful with ST, but the monk was chain pulling without a care in teh world, the SK looks at the mob, and boom its on them.  None of this agro build up nonsence, straight agro continuously on the SK for the entire raid.<br />
<br />
Lastly for a raid such as rumblecrush, who tends to wipe out clerics with rampage when unslowed, we use spam healing at the start until the slow is in, then have a small chain whilst the rest nuke.<br />
<br />
And agree with thistle on ranger, my guilds first klandicar kill was with a ranger tank (who even survived the entire fight) WS is very nice for delaying damage for agro generation purposes.</font></p>
	
