<table bgcolor="#FFFFFF" width="95%" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" border="0"><tr><td width="10"><img width="10" height="1" src="images/space.gif" alt=""></td><td width="100%"><!-- spacer -->

<table cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" border="0" bgcolor=""  width="95%" align="center"><tr><td>
<table cellpadding="4" cellspacing="1" border="0"  width="100%">
<tr>
	<td bgcolor="#F7F7F7" width="175" valign="top" nowrap>
	<a name="post66571"></a>
	
	<font size="2" face="Verdana, Arial"><b>Delheru</b></font><br>
	<font size="1" face="Verdana, Arial">Baron</font><br>
	<p>
	<font size="1" face="Verdana, Arial">Registered: Dec 1999<br>
	Location: Espoo, Finland<br>
	Posts: 479</font></td>
	
	<td bgcolor="#F7F7F7" width="100%" valign="top">
	<font size="1" face="Verdana, Arial"><img src="../ubb/icons/icon1.gif" alt="Post" border="0"> <b></b></font>
	<p><font size="2" face="Verdana, Arial">One thing that would probably deserve a topic of it's own...<br />
<br />
Do people feel that their stats affect agro? I don't mean warrior stats with that, though they help too of course.<br />
<br />
First of all I'm sure everyone knows mobs have temp agro from 'vulnerability'. The two obvious cases for this are being under 40% hp or sitting. Gets serious mob interest, which immediately disappears when you stand or get healed up. Why do I think stats might be involved in this?<br />
<br />
I've been main cleric of a guild that's killed everything there is in EQ for lord knows how long. Well do I remember Vindi or Tormax summoning me after that first CH and promptly raping me. Then I started surviving the summons, and all of a sudden they didn't even bother summoning me anymore. It doesn't matter how fast I land the first CH after the MT has engaged, I just don't get summoned (1sec after AoW engaged is np).<br />
<br />
Thing is newer clerics keep dying quite a bit. I used to scold them about it and basically tell them they're doing something seriously wrong... but after some freaky things like me landing first CH (no summon) and a recruit with 1200 less hp landing next one getting summoned and gibbed, I've begun wondering if stats indeed do play in to the "vulnerability" agro.<br />
<br />
Guess I'll try landing the first heal at next AoW with no gear on to see if I'll get owned.<br />
<br />
-- Delheru Tanreall<br />
<a href="http://www.ascentguild.com" target="_blank">Ascent</a>, Rodcet Nife<br />
<br />
[This message has been edited by Delheru (edited 08-03-2002).]</font></p>
	
