	<td bgcolor="#F7F7F7" width="100%" valign="top">
	<font size="1" face="Verdana, Arial"><img src="../ubb/icons/icon1.gif" alt="Post" border="0"> <b></b></font>
	<p><font size="2" face="Verdana, Arial">Starting the CH about 5 or 6 seconds early on vindi is a good idea. <br />
<br />
Make sure the first cleric in the ch chain is level 60 (lower agro then a 58 cleric for example) and if your cleric is still getting agro try one or more of the following:<br />
<br />
1. Have your MT get a agro boost spell.<br />
2. Have your first CH cleric get a agro lowering spell.<br />
3. Have your first CH cleric slam invul right after he throws the first CH.<br />
<br />
All of these will help you fix your problem.<br />
<br />
What made the difference for us was getting our MT's huge agro weapons. Get a MT who has uber taunt weapons and vindi WILL stay on that MT.<br />
<br />
<br />
Resurrector (Veeshan)<br />
High Priest <br />
Guild Leader of Farstorm<br /></font></p>
	
