	Posts: 432</font></td>
	
	<td bgcolor="#DEDFDF" width="100%" valign="top">
	<font size="1" face="Verdana, Arial"><img src="../ubb/icons/icon1.gif" alt="Post" border="0"> <b></b></font>
	<p><font size="2" face="Verdana, Arial">We also start the chain on the MT before he/she engages the mob.  Usually depending on the mob of course, the Mt engages the mob on the 3rd ch called.<br />
<br />
Agro can be managed a lot of ways.  On rampaging mobs, a soaker can absorb rampage damage and that helps keep clerics off rampage.  A longer Ch chain with a decent enough interval helps manage hate too.  5 clerics at 4 secs is better than 3 at 4, and so on and so forth.<br />
<br />
As someone posted, sitting is a big no no on a lot of mobs.  Hence the necessity of Ft items.  Also, another big agro problem is clerics rodding too low before askign for a heal or tanks running back for heals too low and training clerics. :-( <br />
<br />
Qwenya<br />
